==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Guaiacol
<hw>Guai"a*col</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Guaiac</ets>um + <ets>-ol</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A colorless liquid, <chform>C7H8O2</chform>, with a peculiar odor.
It is the methyl ether of pyrocatechin, and is obtained by distilling
guaiacum from wood-tar creosote, and in other ways. It has been used in
the past for treating pulmonary tuberculosis.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Guaiacum</ent>⟦br⟧
